				 Drunk cop at wheel
 A STAFF REPORTER																								A home guard was arrested on Monday for driving a police van while drunk and knocking down two pedestrians and a motorcyclist at Kankinara, on the citys northern fringes, on Sunday night. The pedestrians, admitted to hospital, are in a serious condition.																								We have arrested Dilip Das for rash driving, said North 24-Parganas police superintendent Supratim Sarkar. The police van has been impounded.																								According to officers, the mishap took place at Narayanpur market around 9pm on Sunday. Das, a home guard of Barrackpore police lines, hit Tapashi Sengupta, 35, and Biswanath Karmakar, 42. Other pedestrians ran away in fear as the van zigzagged down the road.																								The vehicle then hit a motorcycle. Pritam Nandy, the rider, rolled away after falling off. The van pushed the two-wheeler a further 10 ft. A witness said Das was whistling all the while.																								Residents of the area chased the van on their motorcycles and managed to stop it. Das was pulled out of the cabin. On finding him drunk, the enraged residents put up a roadblock. They later informed Jagaddal police station. A team arrived on the spot and arrested Das.																								Sengupta and Karmakar were taken to BN Bose Hospital in Barrackpore for treatment.
